About Cryptex Finance (CTX)

What is Cryptex Finance (CTX)?
Cryptex Finance (CTX) is a decentralized cryptocurrency, started in 2021 by Joe Sticco and the Cryptex Finance team. The CTX token is associated with the Cryptex Finance protocol, which was created to provide tokenized solutions for decentralized finance (DeFi) products, like total market cap indices and synthetic assets.
What can I do with Cryptex Finance (CTX)?
Compatible with the Ethereum network, CTX, pronounced See-Tee-Ex, is an ERC-20 token. You can use CTX to trade and stake digital currencies, as well as participate in the Ethereum network. Cryptex Finances ecosystem is powered by technology called smart contracts.
What is a smart contract?
A smart contract is a digital agreement written in computer code that lives on Ethereums blockchain. It automatically does something when certain conditions are met. For example, if you send me 1 CTX, the smart contract instantly sends you a digital artwork that I created. No human needs to be there to make it work; the smart contract follows the rules it was programmed with.
Why is the Ethereum blockchain important for Cryptex Finance (CTX)?
The Ethereum blockchain network that CTX is compatible with is a huge, secure, ever-growing ledger of smart contract transactions, which everyone can see, and is immutable. Once a traditional smart contract is created, it can't be altered. These types of smart contracts will always follow the original rules that they were programmed with. Upgradable smart contracts allow for changes to be made, adapting to new requirements, or fixing bugs.
What are the most popular uses for Cryptex Finance (CTX)?
Today, Cryptex Finances main use case is for governance of the Cryptex protocol. The CTX token is also used to access financial products like Total Market Cap Token (TCAP), staking, and participation in DeFi dapps. CTX holders are typically community-driven investors and active participants in DeFi protocols.

  • How do I bridge Cryptex Finance (CTX)?

    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging Cryptex Finance (CTX) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging CTX from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap CTX from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.

  • What can you do with Cryptex Finance (CTX)?

    With Cryptex Finance, you can send and receive CTX, the networks native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. CTX is supported in decentralized apps for trading, staking, yield optimization, and payments. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use CTX in select web3 financial strategies, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.

  • How do I trade Cryptex Finance (CTX) for other cryptocurrencies?
